.TH WRBENCH 1
.SH NAME
wrbench \- tool for measuring i/o write throughput.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wrbench
[
.B -l
.I writesize
] [
.B -T
.I totsize
]
[
.I dialstring
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Wrbench
tests the write throughput of a given file or network connection by writing
.I totsize
bytes of data
(default 1 gigabyte)
in
.I writesize
buffers (default 8192 bytes).
.I Wrbench
then prints the amount of time in nanoseconds in the first column and the amount of data written in the second column.
.PP
.I Wrbench
can differentiate between files and dialstrings so
.I dialstring
can also be an undecorated filename.
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/wrbench.c

